og.description:
President Obama quipped today during a visit to Monticello with the French president, That's the good thing about being president, I can do whatever I want.&nbsp;

Via the pool report:


Monticello At 4:45 POTUS and president Hollande walked out from a portico and strolled in Front of your pool with Leslie Bowman, president of the Monticello Foundation. Looking at a terrace she said that Jefferson loved to admire the landscape from there. POTUS said that he'd like to take a look and seemed delighted to break the protocol. That's the good thing as a President, I can do whatever I want he quipped, walking to the terrace with his guest and Ms. Bowman. Pool now in the mansion as the leaders will come and visit Jefferson's study.

